# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ClinicOS — CODEOWNERS  (Phase 10 · DevOps Platform · Part 2)
#
# Maps every path to its accountable reviewer(s). GitHub auto-requests review
# from the matching owner on every PR; combined with branch protection
# ("Require review from Code Owners"), no protected path merges unreviewed.
#
# WHY: the enterprise architecture (ADR-0001) organises the codebase by BOUNDED
# CONTEXT so each module ≈ one team. CODEOWNERS is the machine-readable form of
# that team topology — it routes a change to the people who own that context.
#
# The last matching pattern wins. Order = least → most specific.
# Teams below are placeholders (org teams `@clinic-os/*`); until they exist the
# repo owner is the fallback owner. See docs/devops/GitHubArchitecture.md.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default owner for everything not matched more specifically.
